{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πνίγ-ω</b> [ῑ], <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophron Comicus 68, +others, 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 4.1.6, 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 4.31, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>imperfect</i> ἔπνῑγον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1376: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> πνίξω (ἀπο-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 198, 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 171 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Doric dialect</i> <i>2nd pers.</i> <i>plural</i> <i>future</i> πνιξεῖσθε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Epicharmus Comicus 155: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἔπνιξα, <i>imperative</i> πνῖξον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 27, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.92, Batrachomyomachia 158 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> πνῐγήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “περὶ φυσικῶν δυνάμεων - Scripta Minora” 1.17, (ἀπο-) 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1504, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ νούσων” 3.16; also ἀπο-πεπνίξομαι 4th-5th c.AD: Eunapius Historicus “Vitae Sophistarum” p.463 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἐπνίχθην (ἀπ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων ὀξέων παθῶν” 1.7 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; but ἐπνίγην [ῐ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Batrachomyomachia 148, 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 1.11, (ἀπ-) 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 159, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 512a, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 32.6, etc.: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> πέπνιγμαι, see #11.—The simple verb is less frequently than the <i>compound</i> ἀποπνίγω:— <b>choke, throttle, strangle,</b> Sophr.[same place], etc.; of a doctor, πνίγων.. πικρότατα πόματα διδούς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 522a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἂν ὕλη πνίγῃ [τὸν σῖτον] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 17.14: proverbial, ὅταν τὸ ὕδωρ πνίγῃ, τί δεῖ ἐπιπίνει; 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1146a35 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be choked, stifled,</b> ἐπνιγόμην τὰ σπλάγχνα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1036; αἱ ὑστερικῶς πνιγόμεναι 2nd c.AD: Antyllus Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 10.19.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>impersonal</i> πνίγει, of great heat, <b>it is stifling,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 941b4, 944a7. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>vex, torment,</b> ἕνα χαλκοῦν ἀποβαλὼν αὑτὸν π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Ir.” p.37 W.\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; ὃ δὲ μάλιστά με πνίγει variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Prom.” 17 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>oppress</b> by exactions, 'squeeze', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Misopogon” 368c. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>cook in a close-covered vessel, bake, stew,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.92; δικίδιον.. ἐν λοπάδι πεπνιγμένον 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 511; πεπνιγμένος 5th c.BC: Metagenes Comicus 6. 9. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>drown</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare (πνῖξις 11)\">Refs</a>], in <i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.7.25: _metaphorically_, of plants, τὰ φυτὰ.. τοῖς πολλοῖς [ὕδασι] πνίγεται 1st-2nd c.AD: Pluta